FOSS I KLAKABONDUM • A SLICE OF ICELAND
Barnafossar i Borgarfiroi. Pjosagan segir ao eftir ao tveir
ungir drengir drukknuou hafi mooir peirra sett álög á
steinbrú sem skömmu sidar hrundi i jaroskjálfta.
WATERFALL IN WINTER • A SLICE OF ICELAND
Icelandic folk mythology tells many tales about Barnafossar
in Borgarfjordur. The most famous one is about two
young boys who crossed a natural stone bridge above the
waterfalls. When they drowned at the falls, their mother cast
a spell so that no person could ever cross that bridge. This
natural stone bridge was destroyed in an earthquake shortly
afterwards.
Hákon Már Örvarsson
yfirmatreioslumeistari a Vox
chef de cuisine - Restaurant Vox
Icelandair Saga Class nýtur ráogjafar Hákonar
Orvarssonar, firmatreioslumeistara á Vox Restaurant
á Nordica Hotel i Reykjavik. Vox er nú eitt besta
veitinganus borgarinnar og er Hakon eini islenski
matreiöslumeistarinn sem unnio hefur til verolauna
á Bocuse d'Or keppnini i Lyon i Frakklandi, „Bocuse
de bronze 2001". Hákon starfadi i nokkur ár
sem firmatreiöslumaour á bekktum og virtum
Michelinstjörnu-veitingastao Leu Linster i Frisange i
Luxembourg og starfar nú á Vox i Reykjavik. Okkur er
bad sérstakur heiour ao geta boôio farbegum aõ njóta
serpekkingar og smekkvisi Hakonar.
Hakon Orvarsson, chef de cuisine of Restaurant Vox at
Nordica Hotel in Reykjavik, is the culinary consultant
of Icelandair Business Class. Vox is now regarded as
one of the top restaurants in Reykjavik and Orvarsson
is the only Icelandic chef to win a medal in Bocuse
d'Or, "Bocuse de bronze 2001." Orvarsson worked for
some years as a head chef at Lea Linster's restaurant
in Frisange in Luxembourg which is decorated with
one Michelin star. It is with great pride that we at
Icelandair offer our Business Class passengers the
opportunity to enjoy the culinary expertise of
Hakon Orvarsson.
KEF-USA-7360 / 06-09-12 2005-03 2006
2015.065.007
